				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The seeming read still happens; the 6502 inside the NES just isn't listening. By mapping a shift register that will pay attention to the same bits that the software would, you can make sure <strong>something</strong> listens, and then save the results for the NES. (Is that clear enough?)</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

